		<div class="hr"><hr /></div>
		<p class="intro">Lung disease, also known as respiratory disease, is a category of conditions ranging from asthma to chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) – one of the most common causes of death in England.<sup>1</sup></p>
		<p>COPD is progressive, largely preventable, and strongly linked to deprivation in England. It’s the fifth largest cause of emergency hospital admissions, and an estimated 85 per cent of cases are caused by smoking.<sup>1</sup></p>
