	    <ul class="row">
	        <li class="col col1">
	            <h4>1. Smoking</h4>  
                	        <p>Smoking is a major factor contributing to health inequalities. It damages the lungs and destroys the cells that should protect them. Around half of all smokers develop some airflow obstruction, while 10–20 percent develop COPD.<sup>2</sup>
	            <span class="nice_link"><a href="http://www.nice.org.uk/advice/lgb1" class="external_link" target="_blank">More about smoking-related mortality</a></span>
	        </p>                         
